    <div class="block__content">
      <p>Severe Weather Emergency Provision Protocol for Bournemouth and Poole has been triggered, and will remain in place until further notice.</p>
      <p>When SWEP is activated there are some emergency overnight spaces available in St Stephen's Church, Bournemouth and in the United Reform Church in Poole,</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="block block--highlight">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="block__content">
      <h2 class="h1 best-practice__header">Members of the public are encouraged to:</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Encourage anyone you see rough sleeping in Bournemouth to go to <strong>St Stephens Church Hall, St Stephens Way, BH2 6JZ</strong> at 8:30pm to secure their space for the night. Doors close at 10pm. A number of well-behaved dogs are welcome.</li>
        <li>Encourage anyone you see sleeping rough in Poole to go to <strong>Poole United Reform Church, 36 Skinner Street, BH15 1RH</strong> at 8:30pm to secure their space for the night. Doors close at 10pm. A number of well-behaved dogs are welcome.</li>
        <li>Dial 999 if someone needs emergency help.</li>
        <li>Remember that <a href="https://www.streetlink.org.uk/">Streetlink</a> is not an emergency service - we do not get the referrals immediately so it's best to use <a href="tel:01202315962">01202 315962</a> during periods that SWEP is activated.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="block">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="block__content">
      <p>SWEP is activated when the temperature is forecast to drop below 0 degrees Celsius for three consecutive nights, or when there is severe rain or storms predicted.</p>
